✅ 1. Real-Time Chat System (Like WhatsApp Web)
MongoDB Feature:

Change Streams (real-time updates)

Capped collections

Fast writes

What you can build:

Users send messages

Messages stored in messages collection

A Node.js backend listens for new messages through MongoDB change streams and pushes to frontend

Supports real-time delivery without WebSockets servers getting heavy

Why it’s good:

Teaches you real-time systems

MongoDB handles high message throughput seamlessly

✅ 2. Location-Based Service (Like Zomato / Uber Nearby Driver)
MongoDB Feature:

Geospatial Indexing (2dsphere)

Radius searches (find within X km)

What you can build:

Store driver or restaurant locations

Query:

db.drivers.find({
  location: {
    $near: {
      $geometry: { type: "Point", coordinates: [lng, lat] },
      $maxDistance: 3000
    }
  }
})


Shows drivers within 3 km

Update location every 5 seconds

Why this is OP:

You learn the EXACT feature big companies use for maps

